div.p: Root Cause: The kernel send buffer for fd=5 has space. Since the application has nothing to write but remains registered for EPOLLOUT, epoll_wait returns immediately.
Result: Infinite loop of syscalls. CPU pins 100% on one core.
Mechanism: Once the application-level write_buf is empty, the reactor explicitly removes EPOLLOUT interest from the kernel.
Result: epoll_wait now blocks until new data arrives or a timer expires. CPU utilization drops to near zero.
